//datos de historia {

Monguí is a Colombian municipality located in the province of Sugamuxi in the department of Boyacá.it is located about 97 km from the city of Tunja, capital of the department. It is part of the Network of heritage towns of Colombia.The municipality is bordered to the north by Tópaga and Gámeza, to the east by Mongua and to the south and west by Sogamoso.
Monguí has been highlighted as the most beautiful town in Boyacá and Colombia, a small South American Escorial, cradle of the community action boards.

